Journal Story: Friday is my last day of work. Time for me to go through my gear and pack it up. I have a couple of friends, veterans of the AT, helping me to decide what to take and what to leave.

Have just over two weeks to go before I start my hike. I am busy making last minute preparations. I have bought my plane ticket to Atlanta and arranged for a shuttle to Springer. Going over my gear and getting my trail food figured out. I walk daily and am spoiling myself with a daily sauna. I sure will miss the sauna while on the trail.

Have all my gear shipped off to Atlanta, and I must say it was a wonderful feeling and I didn't even complain about the $50.00+ it cost.Now to plan my schedule. Several of my friends have expressed a interest in hiking a section with me, and I hope it will materialize..
